# m6_p09_snow_drag.shot — M6 P09
#
# Validates the M6 P09 SNOW friction model:
#   - snow_accum grows over the round (5 s at density 1.0 with the
#     SNOW_FULL_S = 60 / density formula gives ~8 % accum; long
#     burst at density 1.0 lets us see full accumulation)
#   - friction lowers as snow piles → mech walking speed drops on
#     the ground
#   - jumping/jetting bypasses snow drag — encourages jet to move
#   - VISIBLE snow pile on top of solid tiles scales with accum
#
# Scenario: Concourse map, weather override = SNOW @ 1.0 (fastest
# accumulation). The mech walks RIGHT for the duration; we screenshot
# at increasing intervals to see the pile grow + the mech slow.
#
# Run:
#   ./soldut --shot tests/shots/m6_p09_snow_drag.shot

window 1920 1080
seed   42 42
out    build/shots/m6_p09_snow_drag

map concourse
weather 1 1.0            # SNOW @ density 1.0 — full accum after ~60 s

# Spawn on the concourse main floor.
spawn_at 1600 1500
mouse    1700 540

# Walk right throughout so we can see how movement degrades.
at  10 press right

# Snapshots show pile growth + mech speed over a generous duration.
# 60 s × 60 ticks = 3600 ticks for full accum, but we can compress
# by reading the early-mid arc.
at  60   shot 1_fresh         #  1 s — snow_accum ≈ 0.017, barely visible
at 600   shot 2_light_pile    # 10 s — snow_accum ≈ 0.17, pile starts to show
at 1800  shot 3_mid_pile      # 30 s — snow_accum ≈ 0.50, clear drag
at 3000  shot 4_thick_pile    # 50 s — snow_accum ≈ 0.83, deep drag
at 3600  shot 5_full_pile     # 60 s — snow_accum ≈ 1.00, max drag

at 3700 release right
at 3720 end

contact_sheet snow_drag cols 3 cell 640 360
